		"description": "<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A makeshift weapon, normally seen in the hands of those who can&rsquo;t make, buy, or scavenge anything better, pipe guns are crude and somewhat unreliable, but effective enough. Bolt-action pipe guns tend to be chambered for rifle caliber rounds, trading rate-of-fire for power and simplicity.</span></p>\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">A Pipe Bolt-Action can accept one each of the following mods. You may not take both a Grip and a Stock Mod. Any Stock mods add the word &ldquo;Rifle&rdquo; to the end of the weapon&rsquo;s name.</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Receiver:</strong> Calibrated, Hardened, Powerful, .38 Receiver, .50 Receiver</li>\n<li><strong>Barrel:</strong> Long Barrel, Ported Barrel, Finned Barrel</li>\n<li><strong>Grip:</strong> Sharpshooter&rsquo;s Grip</li>\n<li><strong>Stock:</strong> Full Stock, Marksman&rsquo;s Stock, RecoilCompensating Stock</li>\n<li><strong>Sights:</strong> Reflex Sight, Short Scope, Long Scope, Short Night Vision Scope, Long Night Vision Scope, Recon Scope</li>\n<li><strong>Muzzle:</strong> Bayonet, Compensator, Muzzle Brake, Suppressor</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
